    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-05-24</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-07-30T21:15:24Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Requires any advertisement for any model of automobile or light duty truck to include the Environmental Protection Agency's Combined Miles Per Gallon Rating, City Miles Per Gallon Rating, Highway Miles Per Gallon Rating MPG, and Estimated Annual Fuel Cost Rating for that model. Treats a violation as an unfair or deceptive act or practice under the Federal Trade Commission Act and requires the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) to enforce this Act.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To require advertising for any automobile model to display information regarding the fuel consumption and fuel cost for that model, and for other purposes.</title>
